`Human` is a type
`Dog` is a type

`Alice` is a `Human`
`Rex` is a `Dog`

`Likes` is a path from
  `A` as type
  `a` as `A`
  `B` as type
  `b` as `B`
  to type

`AliceLikesDogs` is a proof that
  any `d` as `Dog`
  leads to a proof that `Alice` <~ `Likes` ~> `d`

`AliceDoesNotLikeRex` is a proof that
  any proof that `Alice` <~ `Likes` ~> `Rex`
  leads to `False`

// `AliceDoesNotLikeRex` contradicts `AliceLikesDogs`
